706203f-a.folder: Park Avenue & Navy Street, Brooklyn, NY
706203f-a.text:
Park Avenue, east from NAVY =========== Street (something) showing demolition of buildings for the Fort Greene Houses. The area already cleared is the block from St. Edwards Street to North Elliott Place.
Late summer, 1939
Views 1,2
P.L. Sperr

Note: View 3 shows the view(?) east from Navy Street and the Wallabout (?) Houses nearing completion. Views 1,2 are east from St. Edwards Street.

705832f-a.folder: Navy Street & Tillary Street, Brooklyn, NY
705832f-a.text:
Navy Street, north from Tillary Street, toward the Brooklyn Navy Yark. Views 2,3 are at Johnson Street and show demoliton
for the erection of Fort Greene Houses.
P. L. Sperr  View 1: August 23, 1939
NO REPRIDUCTIONS  View 2,3: April 22, 1941
